-- Thailand’s SPCG Completes 30 Megawatts of Solar Power Projects
-- B y   N a t a l i e   O b i k o   P e a r s o n
-- 2012-08-16T03:14:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-16/thailand-s-spcg-completes-30-megawatts-of-solar-power-projects.html
SPCG Pcl (SPCG) ,  Thailand ’s biggest
developer of solar farms, has completed 30 megawatts of sun-
powered capacity, it said in a filing today.  Four projects of 7.46 megawatts each were finished this
month and will start commercial operations on Jan. 31, Chief
Executive Officer Wandee Khunchornyakong said in a statement
sent to the Stock Exchange of Thailand.  The farms have signed contracts to sell their power to the
Provincial Electricity Authority of Thailand, according to the
statement. They will receive a 10-year subsidy of 8 baht (25
cents) per kilowatt-hour, Khunchornyakong said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Natalie Obiko Pearson in Mumbai at 
